From David Karr Subject Re BMW heated grips In article Art Campbell writes Mark Bergman writes To those of you who have the BMW heated handgrips What are they like during the summer Yes you wiseguy I mean while they are off Are they comfortable They're a hard rubber like I always wear some kind of glove fingerless on the hottest Given those two factors They're OK but certainly not When I needed heated grips I made them from pieces of an old bicycle inner tube and a cheap electric heating pad from the drugstore on top of foam grips soft and Cheaper by about a factor of David Karr